            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to calculate and return a monetary value representing the budgeted demand in dollars. The calculation is based on the input parameters, which likely include factors such as quantity, price, and possibly other financial metrics."
